_comment: Coordinates in occluder coordinate system in mm units. Value of key 'requires grad' indicates whether coordinates are assumed to be differentiable. Occluders can be of two types: 'windows' or 'blockers'. Type 'window' means that occlusion happens on the exterior of the boundary. Type 'blocker' means that occlusion happens on the interior of the boundary.
name: default right occluder
